## Objective

Characterise the relationship between probe angle and echo pulse width (TOF) on the HC-SR04 sensor. This validates the core signal theory before integrating into the full arm control system.

**Core hypothesis:**
- Minimum TOF = probe perpendicular to surface
- Increasing TOF = probe increasingly angled
- TOF and amplitude together = reliable perpendicularity indicator

