## Arduino Sketch

File: `src/arduino/hcsr04_tof_distance.ino`

Outputs both TOF (microseconds) and distance (cm) per reading:
```
TOF:1170.0,DIST:20.0
```

TOF is the raw ECHO pin pulse width in microseconds — the round trip travel time of the ultrasound burst. Distance is derived as:
```
distance_cm = TOF_us / 58.0
```

---

## Python Reader

```python
import serial
import time

ser = serial.Serial('/dev/ttyACM0', 9600, timeout=1)
time.sleep(2)

while True:
    line = ser.readline().decode().strip()
    if ',' in line and 'TOF:' in line:
        parts = line.split(',')
        tof  = float(parts[0].replace('TOF:', ''))
        dist = float(parts[1].replace('DIST:', ''))
        if tof > 0:
            print(f'TOF: {tof:.1f} us   DIST: {dist:.1f} cm')
```

