## Implications for Arm Control

| Signal | Used for | Phase |
|---|---|---|
| DIST (cm) | Z height correction | Phase 2 ✅ |
| TOF (µs) | Perpendicularity feedback | Phase 5 ⏳ |
| TOF minimum | Indicates perpendicular alignment | Phase 5 ⏳ |
| TOF trend | Guides forearm_roll correction direction | Phase 5 ⏳ |

**Control strategy for Phase 5:**
```
At each waypoint:
1. Read TOF
2. Nudge forearm_roll by small delta (+/-)
3. Re-read TOF
4. If TOF decreased → continue in same direction
5. If TOF increased → reverse direction
6. Stop when TOF is minimised → perpendicular achieved
```

This is a simple hill-climbing (gradient descent) search on the TOF signal.

