## Limitations of HC-SR04 for Perpendicularity

| Limitation | Impact |
|---|---|
| 40kHz operating frequency | Lower sensitivity than 60kHz transducer |
| Wide beam angle (~15°) | Reduces angular resolution |
| No amplitude output | Can only use TOF, not amplitude |
| ±3mm distance accuracy | Limits minimum detectable angle |

**Planned upgrade:** 60kHz air-coupled ultrasonic transducer which provides both TOF and amplitude, narrower beam, higher sensitivity.

